OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F399A1776877554
OL,3,CTeacher had 'dark thoughts' over
OL,4,Csexually abused adopted baby, court
OL,5,Chears
OL,7,FITV News' Rob Smith has been following
OL,8,Fthe trial of Jamie Varley and John
OL,9,FMcGowan-Fazakerley.
OL,11,FA former high school teacher accused
OL,12,Fof the sexual abuse and murder of an
OL,13,Fadopted baby boy told a friend he had
OL,14,F"dark thoughts" about the youngster, a
OL,15,Fcourt has heard.
OL,17,FJamie Varley, 37, is accused of the
OL,18,Fmurder of 13-month-old Preston Davey,
OL,19,Falong with 25 other charges relating
OL,20,Fto his sexual and physical
OL,21,Fmistreatment.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/12
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,400,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39902
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F399A1776877554
OL,3,CTeacher had 'dark thoughts' over
OL,4,Csexually abused adopted baby, court
OL,5,Chears
OL,7,FHis partner, John McGowan-Fazakerley,
OL,8,F32, is accused of causing or allowing
OL,9,Fthe death of the child and four other
OL,10,Foffences including sexual assault and
OL,11,Fcruelty.
OL,13,FBoth men deny all charges, between
OL,14,FMarch and July 2023.
OL,16,FPreston Crown Court has heard the
OL,17,Fchild was routinely ill-treated,
OL,18,Fsexually abused, physically assaulted
OL,19,Fand had indecent images and videos
OL,20,Ftaken of him during the four months
OL,21,Fthe child was in their care.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/12
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,400,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39903
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F399A1776877554
OL,3,CTeacher had 'dark thoughts' over
OL,4,Csexually abused adopted baby, court
OL,5,Chears
OL,7,FPeter Wright KC, prosecuting, told the
OL,8,Fjury on the second day of the trial
OL,9,Fthat Varley, who had worked as a head
OL,10,Fof year at a high school in Blackpool,
OL,11,Fhad visited a work colleague with the
OL,12,Fbaby.
OL,14,FDuring the visit, a month before the
OL,15,Fchild's death, Varley had "unburdened"
OL,16,Fhimself about not "bonding" with
OL,17,FPreston and struggling with the
OL,18,Fdemands of looking after a baby.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/12
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,400,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39904
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F399A1776877554
OL,3,CTeacher had 'dark thoughts' over
OL,4,Csexually abused adopted baby, court
OL,5,Chears
OL,7,FMr Wright told the jury this included
OL,8,Fhaving "dark thoughts" towards the
OL,9,Fchild, who Varley had renamed Elijah,
OL,10,Fduring the adoption process.
OL,12,FMr Wright said: "He disclosed to her
OL,13,Fthat he had harmful thoughts towards
OL,14,FElijah and had thoughts of drowning
OL,15,Fhim or of suffocating him, but that he
OL,16,Fwould never carry them out."
OL,26,@pD@HOUpD@VO]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/12
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,400,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39905
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F399A1776877554
OL,3,CTeacher had 'dark thoughts' over
OL,4,Csexually abused adopted baby, court
OL,5,Chears
OL,7,FVarley told the woman he had disclosed
OL,8,Fthis as part of welfare checks
OL,9,Finvolving his employer and social
OL,10,Fworkers involved in the adoption of
OL,11,FPreston.
OL,13,FThe court heard the woman only told
OL,14,Fthe police this after the child's
OL,15,Fdeath.
OL,17,FPreston had been born on June 16,
OL,18,F2022, and taken into care by Oldham
OL,19,FCouncil and placed with foster parents.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/12
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,400,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39906
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F399A1776877554
OL,3,CTeacher had 'dark thoughts' over
OL,4,Csexually abused adopted baby, court
OL,5,Chears
OL,7,FThe defendants had applied to Adoption
OL,8,FNow, an organisation that handles
OL,9,Fadoption for local authorities in the
OL,10,FNorth West.
OL,12,FPreston was placed with them to adopt
OL,13,Faged nine-months, living at their home
OL,14,Fon Staining Road, Blackpool after they
OL,15,Fwere approved.
OL,17,FThe court heard he was admitted to
OL,18,Fhospital with injuries three times in
OL,19,Fthe just under four months after being
OL,20,Fadopted.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/12
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,400,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39907
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F399A1776877554
OL,3,CTeacher had 'dark thoughts' over
OL,4,Csexually abused adopted baby, court
OL,5,Chears
OL,7,FPreston died on 27 July 2023. Varley
OL,8,Fwas home alone with him on this day
OL,9,Fand had recorded a video of the child
OL,10,Fon his phone.
OL,12,FIn the video, the child, wearing a
OL,13,Fbabygrow and lying on a double bed,
OL,14,Fappears to have suffered a collapse
OL,15,Fand is in recovery from a period of
OL,16,Fnot breathing.
OL,18,FHis lips had a bluish hue, which a
OL,19,Fconsultant concluded was the tell-tale
OL,20,Fsign of a respiratory failure.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/12
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,400,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39908
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F399A1776877554
OL,3,CTeacher had 'dark thoughts' over
OL,4,Csexually abused adopted baby, court
OL,5,Chears
OL,7,FThe jury was told Varley was silent
OL,8,Fthroughout the clip and did not try to
OL,9,Fhelp the child.
OL,11,FAfter McGowan-Fazakerley returned home
OL,12,Ffrom work less than two hours later,
OL,13,Fthe defendants brought Preston to
OL,14,FBlackpool Victoria Hospital,
OL,15,Funconscious and in a state of cardiac
OL,16,Farrest. Medics could not save him.
OL,18,FVarley claimed he had put the child in
OL,19,Fa baby chair in the bath, then left
OL,20,Fhim for around four minutes and when
OL,21,Fhe returned the child was drowning.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G8/12
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,400,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39909
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F399A1776877554
OL,3,CTeacher had 'dark thoughts' over
OL,4,Csexually abused adopted baby, court
OL,5,Chears
OL,7,FMr Wright said Varley was "hysterical"
OL,8,Fand blaming himself, but claimed this
OL,9,Fwas just a "cover up" act.
OL,11,FPreston was in fact dry, had dry hair
OL,12,Fand did not appear to have swallowed
OL,13,Fany water, the court heard.
OL,15,FA Home Office post-mortem examination
OL,16,Ffound multiple non-accidental,
OL,17,Finternal and external injuries
OL,18,Fincluding to his mouth, throat and
OL,19,Fbottom.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G9/12
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,400,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39910
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F399A1776877554
OL,3,CTeacher had 'dark thoughts' over
OL,4,Csexually abused adopted baby, court
OL,5,Chears
OL,7,FThere were bruises and grazes to his
OL,8,Fhead, face and mouth, upper limbs,
OL,9,Fchest, back and left thigh.
OL,11,FThere was no evidence to support
OL,12,Fnatural disease or drowning as the
OL,13,Fcause of death and the internal
OL,14,Finjuries were caused shortly before
OL,15,Fdeath.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G10/12
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,400,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39911
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F399A1776877554
OL,3,CTeacher had 'dark thoughts' over
OL,4,Csexually abused adopted baby, court
OL,5,Chears
OL,7,FThe post-mortem gave the cause of his
OL,8,Fdeath to be acute upper airways
OL,9,Fobstruction, a result either of a
OL,10,Fsmothering most likely with a hand or
OL,11,Fsoft fabric or by the insertion of an
OL,12,Fobject or objects into his mouth.
OL,14,FMr Wright told jurors both defendants
OL,15,Fhad a "sexual interest" in the child,
OL,16,Fand while Varley is accused of being
OL,17,Fresponsible for the murder, his co-
OL,18,Faccused could and should have
OL,19,Fprotected the child and stopped the
OL,20,Fsexual assaults and cruelty which were
OL,21,Fbecoming increasingly serious.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G11/12
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
